The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Uma close shave

 Bhopal, Nov. 3 (PTI): BJP leader Uma Bharti had a narrow escape today as her helicopter developed a technical snag in Chitrakoot while taking off for the Madhya Pradesh capital.

 The six-seater chopper, owned by the state government, developed a fault in its engine around 4 pm, sources said.

 The helicopter, they said, shook vigorously, following which the pilot decided to land.

 The former chief minister is safe, the sources added.




